01:10:40.153 --> 01:10:42.815
And then write, "The duck flew all the way
to Alaska to meet up

01:10:42.905 --> 01:10:43.985
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:10:44.073 --> 01:10:47.065
"with his friend
who was a polar bear who lived there."

01:10:47.160 --> 01:10:49.401
-"And the polar bear..."
-ANNA: How many of these have you had?

01:10:49.495 --> 01:10:51.986
Doesn't matter. Uh... "The end."

01:10:52.832 --> 01:10:55.414
-That's a strange ending.
-It is, isn't it?

01:10:55.501 --> 01:10:57.412
And you want me to take this over
to Lecture Films?

01:10:57.503 --> 01:10:58.788
-Yeah.
-ASSISTANT: Okay.

01:10:58.880 --> 01:11:01.087
Tell them to film that one this week.

01:11:01.174 --> 01:11:02.380
Okay.

01:11:03.384 --> 01:11:05.045
Tell them it's for kids.

01:11:05.178 --> 01:11:07.134
Kids will love that, won't they?

01:11:07.221 --> 01:11:10.008
Bears and ducks in cars.

01:11:11.100 --> 01:11:13.807
-What's that?
-It's a birthday card for you.

01:11:13.895 --> 01:11:16.011
-You want it?
-Thank you.

01:11:16.397 --> 01:11:19.184
Oh, I came to tell you
that I can't watch a movie with you tonight.

01:11:19.275 --> 01:11:21.391
-Why not?
-'Cause I have a date.

01:11:21.486 --> 01:11:23.067
Who with?

01:11:23.946 --> 01:11:26.562
-Brad Kessler.
-Brad Kessler?

01:11:27.200 --> 01:11:31.034
You know what I think of him.
I think he is the world's biggest douche bag.

01:11:31.120 --> 01:11:32.735
