what is she doing standing up here with me?

01:29:32.993 --> 01:29:36.201
She thinks her kids deserve
the best possible start in life.

01:29:36.288 --> 01:29:37.619
And she's right.

01:29:37.747 --> 01:29:40.409
Yeah. And do you know
what that makes you?

01:29:40.500 --> 01:29:41.706
You're a sperm donor.

01:29:41.793 --> 01:29:42.953
(CHUCKLING)

01:29:43.086 --> 01:29:44.496
(GUESTS MURMURING)

01:29:44.963 --> 01:29:46.828
She's my best friend.

01:29:47.924 --> 01:29:49.505
I thought I was your best friend.

01:29:49.634 --> 01:29:51.420
Not now. Let's...

01:29:53.847 --> 01:29:55.462
And I love her.

01:29:56.600 --> 01:29:58.136
Don't do this.

01:29:58.435 --> 01:29:59.925
Don't do it.

01:30:01.187 --> 01:30:03.519
Is this what you really want?

01:30:03.857 --> 01:30:05.267
It's the way of the world, Mark.

01:30:05.358 --> 01:30:08.270
Why? Why does it have to be?

01:30:08.862 --> 01:30:10.773
Who says your kids will be better than mine?

01:30:10.864 --> 01:30:14.982
Who says that a strong jawline or
a fast metabolism or a muscular physique...

01:30:15.118 --> 01:30:16.278
He's also taller.

01:30:16.369 --> 01:30:18.360
No, I know, but I'm just...

01:30:19.831 --> 01:30:21.617
Please, man, I...

01:30:23.001 --> 01:30:26.084
Who says those traits will make your kids
better than mine, or happier?

01:30:26.171 --> 01:30:27.786
I'll love our children.

01:30:27.881 --> 01:30:28.961
And who says you'll make a better husband

01:30:29.049 --> 01:30:32.086
just because you come from
a more privileged family

01:30:32.177 --> 01:30:34.338
or a better genetic line?

01:30:34.804 --> 01:30:36.044
(SIGHS)

01:30:36.306 --> 01:30:39.890
She's a prize on your arm.
And your kids will be, too.

01:30:41.353 --> 01:30:42.513
Anna.

01:30:44.189 --> 01:30:47.681
If you tell me this is what you really want,
I'll go.

01:30:50.904 --> 01:30:51.984
Is this what you really want?

01:30:52.072 --> 01:30:54.734
Well, now, it's not up to us
to decide what we get in life.

01:30:54.866 --> 01:30:58.484
-That's up to the man in the sky.
-I'm talking to her.

01:30:59.537 --> 01:31:02.654
Why don't you just ask the man in the sky
what he wants for Anna?

01:31:02.749 --> 01:31:05.456
-Surely he knows best.
-She knows what's best.

01:31:05.543 --> 01:31:07.659
Just tell her
what the man in the sky wants, Mark.

01:31:07.754 --> 01:31:11.667
Why don't you tell me
what the man in the sky wants for us, Mark?

01:31:11.758 --> 01:31:13.669
Just please tell me.

01:31:14.886 --> 01:31:16.217
(SCOFFS)

01:31:16.429 --> 01:31:17.544
No.

01:31:25.063 --> 01:31:26.769
(GUESTS MURMURING)

01:31:28.900 --> 01:31:30.185
(SIGHS)

01:31:33.405 --> 01:31:34.394
Are we married yet?

01:31:34.531 --> 01:31:37.113
-Because I have plans later.
-There's a few...

01:32:02.809 --> 01:32:04.549
ANNA: Mark, wait!

01:32:06.312 --> 01:32:10.100
Why don't you just tell me
what the man in the sky wants?

01:32:11.443 --> 01:32:13.229
-I did a bad thing.
-It's okay.

01:32:13.319 --> 01:32:16.652
-You're allowed three.
-No, you don't understand.

01:32:18.908 --> 01:32:21.069
There is no man in the sky.

01:32:25.248 --> 01:32:27.409
Why did you say there was?

01:32:30.003 --> 01:32:34.042
I couldn't stand the look on my mum's face
when she was dying.

01:32:34.299 --> 01:32:36.961
And things just escalated.

01:32:39.471 --> 01:32:42.383
But how did you say something that wasn't?

01:32:42.474 --> 01:32:45.637
I don't know, I just did. I just can.

01:32:46.102 --> 01:32:48.218
But when I asked you if being rich

01:32:48.313 --> 01:32:51.601
and successful and famous
changed your genetics,

01:32:51.983 --> 01:32:54.224
why didn't you just say yes?

01:32:55.320 --> 01:32:57.436
'Cause it wouldn't count.

01:33:00.325 --> 01:33:01.485
Mark.

01:33:04.412 --> 01:33:05.743
I know what I want.

01:33:05.830 --> 01:33:07.115
(SIGHS)

01:33:10.293 --> 01:33:13.080
I want little fat kids with snub noses.

01:33:20.512 --> 01:33:22.002
I'm your man.

01:33:35.360 --> 01:33:38.022
MARK: So that's it. I got the girl.

01:33:38.530 --> 01:33:41.772
Anna and I are very happy together,
by the way.

01:33:41.866 --> 01:33:45.529
She still doesn't fully understand
how I said or did all those things.

01:33:45.662 --> 01:33:49.496
No one does.
I'm still the only person who can tell a lie.

01:33:49.624 --> 01:33:52.787
Actually, that's not entirely true.

01:33:55.713 --> 01:33:57.499
What do you think?

01:33:59.008 --> 01:34:00.714
That looks good.

01:34:03.513 --> 01:34:05.629
It tastes so good, Mom my.

01:34:06.015 --> 01:34:08.882
-Your best yet.
-I'm so glad you like it.

01:34:09.394 --> 01:34:10.884
Huh? Oh.

01:34:15.733 --> 01:34:17.974
I don't know where to start.

01:34:18.486 --> 01:34:22.820
Just start on the bread, maybe,
then work my way up there.

01:34:23.366 --> 01:34:27.735
You eat that. You liked it so much.
Why don't you eat some more?

01:34:29.539 --> 01:34:30.449
He loves it.

